<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="140" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d140">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">548.D1/289</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 4301</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-19">March 19, 1936</date>.<lb/>[Received March
                                28.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit herewith
                            Circular Letter No. 57<note n="1" xml:id="d140fn1">Not printed.</note>
                            addressed to you on March 18, 1936 by the Secretary General of the
                            League of Nations, informing you that the proposed Inter-Governmental
                            Conference for the adoption of the legal status of refugees coming from
                            Germany will meet at Geneva on July second next. The Secretary General
                            desires to be informed before May 15 whether the American Government
                            intends to be represented at this Conference, and by whom. A copy of the
                            provisional program is enclosed.<note n="2" xml:id="d140fn2">Not
                                attached to file copy.</note></p>
                        <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                        <closer>For the Minister:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stanley
                                    Hawks</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>